history.text: Hello!
Hey I just saw The new del Toro film, The Shape of Water!  It has a really high rating on Rotten Tomatoes!
It does! And I agree, it was excellent!
Cinema Score gave it an A
Doe you agree with that rating?
I really do!  Did you like Sally Hawkins as the mute cleaner who works for the government?
I did, she was spectacular!
How did you fee about Michael Shannon as Strickland?

Oh Michael Shannon was great! Very compelling. 
I have read alot of critics on it too... they are overall pretty positive reviews.  One said it was a 'powerful vision... joyously free;
The cinematography was beautiful
I would expect no less from Guillermo del Toro, the director.
He deserved that Oscar!
I was unaware of that!  I do know that Octavia Spencer was also in the film.  She was very good as a co-worker of Elisa's character.
She was good
I felt her story line was a little under developed tho
I could always use to see more of her!  I did love the use of sign language in the film!  It was so tenderly done.
It was, I agree
I love that they didn't subtitle it

I did feel that Octavia
s

Richard Spencer was astounding as the neighbor/friend too.  They dealt with his closeted nature well, I think... but I would have loved more development there.  Did they not subtitle it?  I must not have noticed that.
Octavia's part was a little sterotypical though
I don't remember there being subtitles, but I could be wrong?
I thought the bond with the creature was developed well with her visiting him secretly, so intimate
I love Richard Jenkins in everything he does
Jenkins!  yes.  I always get his name wrong.  I was FREAKED at the cat scene...
I know!! I was so sad!! Poor Pandora
But I love that he didn't freak out
Yes, it showed his true tender heart.  The scene in the theatre downstairs was gorgeous
It was a gorgeous space! And the scene was so touching

The scene where she filled up her bathroom gave me anx
iety lol
I thought the whole sex scene would be awkward, but it was quite lovely.
like, you are on a second floor apt, that is too much weight for a bathroom to handle lol
OH I agree! And I love her explanation to Octavia about how lol
LOL.  Did you totally sympathize with the RUssian spy guy. Mosenkov?
I did eventually, I enjoyed his character arc
Very much... I was even sad for him when he dies...
Same!
The use of the scars as gills made me gasp!  Like, I should have seen that coming!
They payoff was great on Strickland's death
*the
Oh I agree!! Like, he made them into gills! [tears]
Oh yes... I was waiting for him to die for a while!
Me too! They really made you despise him
Oh yes.  The voiceover worked really well to tie it together too.
It did!
I love how Giles assumes she had her happily ever after but for all he knew she died and was sinking to the ocean floor
LOL I never thought of that, but I'm glad WE got to see the gills thing...
Me too!
like he wasn't sure that the creature survived so how could he have known that he healed her down there
The actors voice is so comforting, I was willing to believe him. even if I hadn't seen it.
Me too
I think that's it... it's been nice chatting!
